<br>
I really like both of these classes from what I've read. They have many similarities. Both can heal and rezz, both have haste spells(enhancement spec for friars, nurture spec for wardens) and both seem like good fighters.<br>
<br>
From what I've been reading here it sounds like friars put out some serious damage but I have no idea how wardens fair. Wardens are limited to blades and blunt weapons which I don't know if they do a lot less damage than staffs, just a bit less or on par.<br>
<br>
One reason I'm leaning toward warden is because of the group movement speed enhancement that is in the nurture specialty. I've read how movement is very slow in DAoC so any improvement on that would be nice. Another thing wardens get in the regrowth spec is what seems to be a regeneration spell but I'm not sure. The first one is called Solar Conversion and says  &quot;Caster's health buffed 2 every cycle&quot;. Sounds like a watered down shaman/druid regen spell but I'm not sure. How many HP do you typically have at say 10th lvl and is 2 per cycle noticeable?<br>
<br>
Last thing. Anyone know of a website for wardens with information that my help answer my questions? <br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
